WEBVTT

00:01.330 --> 00:03.210
There's something
we need to talk about.

00:03.210 --> 00:04.540
It's about Charlie and me.

00:04.540 --> 00:05.750
Gary: When you're young,

00:05.750 --> 00:07.670
you think adults
have it all figured out.

00:07.670 --> 00:09.670
You spoke at his funeral!

00:09.670 --> 00:11.790
I trusted you!

00:11.790 --> 00:13.460
If only that were true.

00:13.460 --> 00:14.540
About the night Chad died.

00:14.540 --> 00:16.120
Eric has
your brother's heart.

00:16.120 --> 00:18.670
It seems to me
we're all works in progress.

00:18.670 --> 00:21.380
You keep saying you need to know
who you are without cancer.

00:21.380 --> 00:23.330
Maybe I need to figure out
who I am without you.

00:23.330 --> 00:24.460
We make mistakes...

00:24.460 --> 00:26.120
Gary, if you're gonna be
this sexually active,

00:26.120 --> 00:27.420
you need to be careful.

00:27.420 --> 00:28.790
...but that's part of life.

00:28.790 --> 00:30.750
Hey!
That's a stop sign!

00:30.750 --> 00:33.000
I haven't been with anyone
since Chloe.

00:33.000 --> 00:34.540
What really matters...

00:34.540 --> 00:36.750
I'm gonna tell her.
Now is not the right time.

00:36.750 --> 00:38.000
...is what you do next.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.210
Take care of her.
We will.

00:40.210 --> 00:42.250
I want to adopt a baby.

00:42.250 --> 00:43.790
I want to save someone,
too.

00:43.790 --> 00:46.170
[ Both chuckle ]

00:46.170 --> 00:48.000
♪♪

00:48.000 --> 00:50.080
Okay.

00:50.080 --> 00:51.880
Oh, hey.
[ Chuckles ]

00:51.880 --> 00:53.250
I'm Rome.
And I'm Regina.

00:53.250 --> 00:54.580
Both:
And we're the Howards.

00:54.580 --> 00:56.710
What are you doing?
Huh?
What you told me to do.

00:56.710 --> 00:59.830
No. I said that we can't say
"We're the Howards" together.

00:59.830 --> 01:01.500
It's creepy.

01:01.500 --> 01:03.040
Seriously,
would you let people

01:03.040 --> 01:05.080
who said things at the same time
like that adopt your baby?

01:05.080 --> 01:06.620
No.

01:06.620 --> 01:08.580
[ Camera beeps ]
Any other notes,
Mr. Spielberg?

01:08.580 --> 01:10.790
Now that you mention it,
you --

01:10.790 --> 01:13.670
No.
I love what you're doing.

01:13.670 --> 01:15.750
Especially when you sit up
straight like that.

01:15.750 --> 01:17.250
[ Clears throat ]

01:17.250 --> 01:18.670
I'm sorry.

01:18.670 --> 01:21.170
It's just, you heard what
the lady at the agency said.

01:21.170 --> 01:22.620
Thousands of people
are trying to adopt,

01:22.620 --> 01:25.000
and if our video doesn't stand
out, we'll never get selected.

01:25.000 --> 01:26.290
[ Inhales deeply ]

01:26.290 --> 01:27.880
Okay.

01:27.880 --> 01:29.290
Let's do this.

01:29.290 --> 01:30.460
Thank you.
Yeah.

01:30.460 --> 01:32.290
All right.
Okay.

01:32.290 --> 01:33.920
Okay.
[ Camera beeps ]

01:33.920 --> 01:35.670
All right, let's do this thing.
And...

01:37.210 --> 01:37.960
Action.

01:37.960 --> 01:38.790
Yeah.

01:38.790 --> 01:40.040
Oh, hey.

01:40.040 --> 01:41.170
I'm Regina.

01:41.170 --> 01:42.210
Ugh.

01:43.670 --> 01:46.210
[ Both laugh, camera beeps ]

01:46.210 --> 01:48.250
Delilah:
We're gonna get through this,

01:48.250 --> 01:49.830
and we're gonna be
better off for it.

01:49.830 --> 01:51.500
Mm-hmm.

01:51.500 --> 01:52.750
Think about it, Charlie.

01:52.750 --> 01:54.620
After we're done
with your sleep training,

01:54.620 --> 01:56.500
when you wake up
in the middle of the night,

01:56.500 --> 01:58.080
you won't need to
cry for Mommy anymore.

01:58.080 --> 02:00.040
Mnh-mnh.

02:00.040 --> 02:04.250
You're gonna be a strong,
independent young woman
[ Fussing ]

02:04.250 --> 02:05.920
ready to take on the world.

02:05.920 --> 02:07.580
[ Fussing continues ]

02:07.580 --> 02:10.000
Or at least ready to let Mommy
sleep five, six hours,

02:10.000 --> 02:11.960
'cause Mommy really
needs her sleep.

02:11.960 --> 02:13.830
[ Crying ]

02:13.830 --> 02:15.250
We're doing it.

02:15.250 --> 02:17.210
We're doing it.
We're doing it, baby.

02:17.210 --> 02:18.830
You got this, sweetie.

02:18.830 --> 02:21.120
And we're making this video
to show you who we are

02:21.120 --> 02:23.790
and why Rome and I
are so excited

02:23.790 --> 02:27.080
to make a child
part of our family.

02:27.080 --> 02:28.830
And cut!
[ Camera beeps ]

02:28.830 --> 02:30.830
That was amazing.

02:30.830 --> 02:33.170
Took, like, 17 takes --
nailed it.

02:33.170 --> 02:34.170
[ Chuckles ]

02:34.170 --> 02:35.120
Sophie:
Totally nailed it.

02:36.670 --> 02:39.000
[ Crunching ]

02:39.000 --> 02:41.500
Hey.
Hey.

02:41.500 --> 02:43.670
How long you been, uh,
back there crunching?

02:43.670 --> 02:46.170
[ Muffled ]
Just for this last take.

02:46.170 --> 02:47.420
The good one?

02:47.420 --> 02:49.920
Maybe no one will notice.
Yep.

02:49.920 --> 02:52.500
I'm sure no one will notice
some random teenage girl

02:52.500 --> 02:54.380
just chomping on corn flakes
in our kitchen.

02:54.380 --> 02:56.040
Oh, hey, I meant to ask --

02:56.040 --> 02:57.500
I have a calculus test
next week,

02:57.500 --> 02:58.620
and I could really
use some help.

02:58.620 --> 03:00.460
Uh...

03:00.460 --> 03:02.830
No, relax.
I-I didn't mean from you guys.

03:02.830 --> 03:05.500
Are you sure? 'Cause -- 'Cause
if you really need help,

03:05.500 --> 03:07.000
Regina's right here.
[ Scoffs ]

03:07.000 --> 03:08.710
Actually, I wanted to know
if my friend Jess

03:08.710 --> 03:10.540
could come over tomorrow
and maybe help me study.

03:10.540 --> 03:11.790
Sure.

03:11.790 --> 03:13.750
Uh, w-wait, wait, wait.

03:13.750 --> 03:16.580
So, uh, this Jess...

03:16.580 --> 03:18.710
is he a he?

03:18.710 --> 03:20.540
No, she's a she.

03:20.540 --> 03:23.120
Oh. Okay. Oh.

03:23.120 --> 03:25.080
Love Jess. Support Jess.
Team Jess!

03:25.080 --> 03:26.540
[ Chuckles ] Thanks.

03:26.540 --> 03:27.960
Whew!

03:27.960 --> 03:30.380
Is it me,
or is this parenting thing

03:30.380 --> 03:32.040
not as hard
as everyone says it is?

03:33.620 --> 03:34.920
[ Charlie crying ]

03:34.920 --> 03:42.540
♪♪

03:42.540 --> 03:49.960
♪♪

03:49.960 --> 03:52.170
[ Crying stops ]

03:57.750 --> 03:58.920
[ Floorboard creaks ]

03:58.920 --> 04:01.580
[ Crying resumes ]

04:01.580 --> 04:05.580
♪♪

04:05.580 --> 04:06.790
[ Sighs ]

04:06.790 --> 04:08.500
[ Blinds rattle ]

04:10.960 --> 04:12.250
Jackie:
Good. You're awake.

04:12.250 --> 04:13.830
There's your pants,
there's your phone.

04:13.830 --> 04:14.960
There's the door.

04:16.420 --> 04:18.750
Yeah, that's what
I was gonna say.

04:18.750 --> 04:20.250
Last night was fun,
but I should probably just --

04:20.250 --> 04:21.380
[ Door opens, closes ]

04:21.380 --> 04:22.170
...go.

04:23.880 --> 04:25.500
[ Sighs ]

04:25.500 --> 04:27.710
Okay, three minutes away.

04:32.210 --> 04:33.620
Oh, no.

04:33.620 --> 04:35.710
Ah, no.
No, no, no!

04:35.710 --> 04:36.880
Uh, excuse me.

04:36.880 --> 04:38.920
Sorry to bother you,
but my phone just died.

04:38.920 --> 04:40.460
I really need --
Here.

04:43.120 --> 04:44.120
What, do I look homeless?

04:45.750 --> 04:47.960
I'm keeping this!

04:51.170 --> 04:52.670
[ Sighs ]

04:55.330 --> 05:01.380
♪♪

05:01.380 --> 05:03.330
I'm so--
I'm sorry.
No, um...

05:03.330 --> 05:04.960
I ju-- No, I thought --
I'm sorry.

05:04.960 --> 05:07.620
[ Chuckles ]

05:07.620 --> 05:09.040
[ Sighs ]

05:13.580 --> 05:14.620
[ Sighs ]

05:14.620 --> 05:16.750
[ Line ringing ]

05:16.750 --> 05:17.790
[ Click ]

05:17.790 --> 05:20.120
Hey. It's me.

05:20.120 --> 05:23.380
Uh, can you meet up?

05:23.380 --> 05:26.580
I'm -- I'm trying to write
this article about loss,

05:26.580 --> 05:30.000
and I would love
to get your opinion.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.080
Yeah, one for the club.
Great.

05:34.120 --> 05:35.830
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

05:35.830 --> 05:36.620
Hi.

05:36.620 --> 05:37.880
Oh. Hey, Dakota.

05:37.880 --> 05:38.880
They'll be a few minutes,
okay?

05:38.880 --> 05:40.120
Thanks.

05:40.120 --> 05:44.210
♪♪

05:44.210 --> 05:45.620
He's lying.

05:45.620 --> 05:47.670
What?

05:47.670 --> 05:50.170
He said it'll be a few minutes,
but it'll be more like 12.

05:50.170 --> 05:51.080
[ Chuckles ]

05:53.290 --> 05:55.170
So, are you
a musician, too?

05:55.170 --> 05:57.580
Yeah. You ever
hear of the Red Ferns?

05:57.580 --> 05:58.880
Nope.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.380
Okay,
so that makes you...

06:00.380 --> 06:01.210
Cool?

06:01.210 --> 06:02.210
Pbht.
[ Laughs ]

06:02.210 --> 06:03.580
I was gonna say "young."

06:03.580 --> 06:05.920
Sorry. I tend to get snarky
when I'm nervous.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.210
Have you worked with these guys
for a long time?

06:09.210 --> 06:10.880
I actually haven't worked
with them for a while.

06:10.880 --> 06:12.420
I reached out to Trevor

06:12.420 --> 06:14.460
because I used to have a deal
here with my band.

06:14.460 --> 06:15.920
Wait.

06:15.920 --> 06:17.210
Are you in the Red Ferns?

06:17.210 --> 06:18.080
Oh, so you have
heard of us.

06:18.080 --> 06:19.330
Yeah.
Can I get a selfie?

06:19.330 --> 06:21.000
[ Chuckles ]

06:21.000 --> 06:22.580
So, have I heard
any of your songs?

06:22.580 --> 06:25.000
Well, there was
"Be My Katie."

06:25.000 --> 06:26.290
Wrote that for my wife.

06:26.290 --> 06:28.040
Uh, "Eyes Don't Lie."

06:28.040 --> 06:29.460
Miss.

06:29.460 --> 06:32.330
Uh, last year, I wrote a song
called "Unexpected."

06:32.330 --> 06:33.750
"Unexpected"?

06:33.750 --> 06:35.580
I love that song.

06:35.580 --> 06:36.460
♪ This was unexpected ♪

06:36.460 --> 06:37.880
Yeah!

06:37.880 --> 06:39.790
♪ I blinked,
and I missed it ♪
Wow.

06:39.790 --> 06:41.080
I can't believe
you wrote that!

06:43.210 --> 06:45.080
Wow.

06:45.080 --> 06:47.580
Your meeting's gonna go
a lot better than mine.

06:47.580 --> 06:49.580
I'm pretty sure all these people
think I'm a hack

06:49.580 --> 06:51.750
and that I'm gonna
get dropped today.

06:51.750 --> 06:54.120
Or tomorrow. The point is,
you will not last the week.

06:54.120 --> 06:55.420
What?

06:55.420 --> 06:57.500
I'm kidding.
[ Chuckles ]

06:57.500 --> 07:00.290
Trevor has amazing taste.
He would never sign a hack.

07:00.290 --> 07:01.500
I thought you said
he signed you.

07:01.500 --> 07:02.920
[ Chuckles ]

07:02.920 --> 07:05.040
Okay. Dakota,
they're ready for you.

07:05.040 --> 07:06.080
Michael will take you back.

07:06.080 --> 07:08.210
Look at that.
They called you first.

07:08.210 --> 07:10.170
♪ This is unexpected ♪
[ Chuckles ]

07:10.170 --> 07:12.290
Hey, seriously, though,
good luck.

07:12.290 --> 07:13.380
Thanks.

07:13.380 --> 07:15.540
You, too, Red Ferns.
Mm.

07:15.540 --> 07:16.620
Hi.

07:16.620 --> 07:18.040
Stevie: So, Eddie.
Yeah?

07:18.040 --> 07:20.540
Unfortunately, Trevor got
pulled into something.

07:20.540 --> 07:21.670
He's gonna have to
reschedule.

07:21.670 --> 07:22.670
Oh, really?

07:22.670 --> 07:23.880
Yeah, sorry.

07:23.880 --> 07:25.620
We'll be in touch.

07:25.620 --> 07:29.080
♪♪

07:29.080 --> 07:31.960
-Hey, how are you?
-Yes, please. Thank you.

07:31.960 --> 07:34.710
-Thank you. Enjoy your day.
-Thank you.

07:34.710 --> 07:37.120
[ Sighs ]

07:37.120 --> 07:38.830
Hi, there.
What can I get for you?

07:38.830 --> 07:40.420
I just need to borrow
one of those chargers.

07:40.420 --> 07:42.670
Ooh, sorry. Chargers are
for customers only.

07:43.880 --> 07:45.670
[ Sighing ]
Okay. I'll take this.

07:45.670 --> 07:46.540
Who am I kidding?

07:46.540 --> 07:48.000
[ Laughs ]

07:48.000 --> 07:50.210
I'll take these.

07:50.210 --> 07:51.960
Ooh, sorry.
Our machine is down.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.290
Do you have cash?

07:53.290 --> 07:56.290
Do I have cash?
Of course I have...cash.

07:56.290 --> 07:58.880
Uh, what can I get
for $1?

07:58.880 --> 08:00.420
Nothing.
Really?

08:00.420 --> 08:03.460
Not even a squirt of,
uh, pumpkin spice?

08:03.460 --> 08:04.540
That's, uh, seasonal.

08:04.540 --> 08:05.620
Isn't it the season?

08:05.620 --> 08:06.960
The season starts tomorrow.

08:06.960 --> 08:09.040
You're killing me, man.
I just need to charge my phone.

08:09.040 --> 08:10.380
I got him.

08:10.380 --> 08:11.540
Hey, man.

08:11.540 --> 08:13.170
Eric.

08:13.170 --> 08:16.580
Ha! Thanks for being a part
of my favorite day ever.

08:16.580 --> 08:17.580
Gary.

08:17.580 --> 08:18.830
Rough morning, huh?

08:18.830 --> 08:21.000
Well, we can't all be
Mr. Perfect.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.830
Look at you, exercising
with another man's heart.

08:23.830 --> 08:25.540
Your doctor
must be very proud.

08:25.540 --> 08:26.670
Or mad.

08:26.670 --> 08:28.580
I mean, I don't know
what you're allowed to do

08:28.580 --> 08:30.580
with another person's organ.
[ Chuckles ]

08:30.580 --> 08:32.540
That sounded more sexual
than I intended it.

08:32.540 --> 08:34.880
[ Sighs ]

08:34.880 --> 08:35.750
[ Clears throat ]

08:35.750 --> 08:37.330
Uh...

08:37.330 --> 08:39.790
Hey, man, uh...

08:39.790 --> 08:41.500
I never got a chance
to --

08:41.500 --> 08:44.580
to tell you
how sorry I am about...

08:44.580 --> 08:47.250
how everything went down
with -- with you and Maggie.

08:47.250 --> 08:49.750
I hope I wasn't a-a factor
in all that.

08:49.750 --> 08:51.380
Ah, don't be silly.

08:51.380 --> 08:53.500
You split up Maggie and her mom,
not Maggie and me.

08:54.710 --> 08:57.290
Well, it doesn't matter.
I've moved on.

08:57.290 --> 08:59.380
I'm --
I'm glad to hear that.

08:59.380 --> 09:01.580
Cappuccino
and a soy milk latte.

09:01.580 --> 09:03.120
Oh, that's me.

09:03.120 --> 09:07.380
♪♪

09:07.380 --> 09:08.880
Um...

09:08.880 --> 09:10.000
see you around, Gary.

09:11.540 --> 09:12.750
Yeah.

09:23.380 --> 09:26.080
The partners are gathering
in the conference
room in 10 minutes.

09:26.080 --> 09:27.420
You got this.
Thanks, Carter.

09:27.420 --> 09:28.960
And don't forget
you promised Theo

09:28.960 --> 09:31.170
you'd pick up new strings
for his guitar.

09:31.170 --> 09:32.580
Oh, shoot.
I don't have time --

09:32.580 --> 09:34.830
Yonk!

09:34.830 --> 09:36.880
[ Gasps ]
How did you know?

09:36.880 --> 09:38.290
He's been breaking them
so often,

09:38.290 --> 09:39.620
I just ordered
a half a dozen online.

09:39.620 --> 09:41.210
Easy peasy.

09:41.210 --> 09:42.750
Have I told you
you're the best?

09:42.750 --> 09:46.170
You have, but, uh,
raises speak louder than words.

09:46.170 --> 09:47.170
Hmm.

09:47.170 --> 09:50.080
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

09:50.080 --> 09:51.330
[ Cellphone beeps ]

09:51.330 --> 09:53.040
Hello?
Katherine?

09:53.040 --> 09:56.170
It's Principal Taylor
from E. Melvin Elementary.

09:56.170 --> 09:58.460
Is everything okay?

09:58.460 --> 10:00.170
Actually, no.
[ School bell rings ]

10:00.170 --> 10:01.920
Uh,
Theo's been in a fight.

10:01.920 --> 10:03.960
What?
We need you to
come down to the school.

10:05.920 --> 10:09.540
Of course.
I'll be there right away.

10:09.540 --> 10:11.170
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:13.620 --> 10:16.420
It's counterintuitive,
but she's taking a long nap now

10:16.420 --> 10:18.000
so she's not
overtired.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.710
Otherwise, she won't
fall asleep tonight.

10:19.710 --> 10:21.380
Babies are hard.

10:21.380 --> 10:23.580
Especially when they're 16
and not talking to you.

10:23.580 --> 10:25.880
Oh.
How's all that going?

10:25.880 --> 10:27.830
It's tough.

10:27.830 --> 10:29.170
But you were right.

10:29.170 --> 10:31.750
Some space is good,
and...

10:31.750 --> 10:33.710
she's in good hands
with Gina and Rome.

10:33.710 --> 10:34.710
She is.

10:34.710 --> 10:36.460
And you're doing
the right thing.

10:36.460 --> 10:38.210
Thanks.

10:38.210 --> 10:39.920
But that's not
why you're here.

10:39.920 --> 10:41.080
You're here to talk about
your article,

10:41.080 --> 10:43.080
and really,
it's fantastic.

10:43.080 --> 10:44.420
Can you please
tell my editor that?

10:44.420 --> 10:45.670
He wants me to make
all these changes.

10:45.670 --> 10:48.080
He wants the last line to be
more of a "gut punch,"

10:48.080 --> 10:49.580
whatever that means.

10:49.580 --> 10:51.670
Well, I'm sure
you can figure it out.

10:51.670 --> 10:53.210
You've been crushing it.

10:53.210 --> 10:55.460
Working, writing,
traveling.

10:55.460 --> 10:57.620
You're just finding
the perfect balance --

10:57.620 --> 10:59.120
I kissed Eric.

11:02.290 --> 11:04.210
I'm sorry that Trevor canceled.
That sucks.

11:04.210 --> 11:05.210
Thanks.

11:05.210 --> 11:06.500
Are you sure it's okay

11:06.500 --> 11:08.330
you're missing the meeting
with the partners?

11:08.330 --> 11:10.210
It'll have to be.
Theo comes first.

11:11.830 --> 11:13.750
[ Door opens ]

11:13.750 --> 11:14.960
Thanks for coming in.

11:17.790 --> 11:21.420
I just have to say, I know there
are two sides to every story,

11:21.420 --> 11:24.330
but Theo is the smallest kid
in the class.

11:24.330 --> 11:26.880
For a student to be bullied
on school grounds

11:26.880 --> 11:29.000
under your watch
is completely unacceptable.

11:29.960 --> 11:31.620
I totally agree.

11:32.830 --> 11:34.000
Thing is...

11:34.000 --> 11:36.420
Theo's the one
who started it.

11:36.420 --> 11:37.500
What?

11:37.500 --> 11:39.620
He pushed another boy
to the floor.

11:39.620 --> 11:44.330
♪♪

11:44.330 --> 11:46.000
I was so embarrassed.

11:46.000 --> 11:48.170
I just ran out of there.

11:48.170 --> 11:50.580
I mean, it's just a kiss.
It's not that big a deal, right?

11:50.580 --> 11:53.620
Well, I mean, last time I kissed
someone, I got pregnant.

11:53.620 --> 11:55.920
[ Chuckles ]

11:55.920 --> 11:58.420
He hasn't been with anyone
since his fiancée died.

11:58.420 --> 12:00.210
And to be honest,
I'm confused.

12:00.210 --> 12:01.670
I mean, one minute,

12:01.670 --> 12:04.250
I am swiping my way
through the Boston dating scene.

12:04.250 --> 12:06.170
The next minute,
I am kissing the guy

12:06.170 --> 12:08.580
who has
my brother's heart.

12:08.580 --> 12:10.210
Then there's Gary,
and --

12:11.500 --> 12:13.210
What about Gary?

12:14.500 --> 12:16.420
I don't know.

12:16.420 --> 12:19.250
I guess I just always...

12:19.250 --> 12:21.330
thought that eventually,
we would end up together.

12:23.460 --> 12:25.420
And now who even knows?
[ Chuckles ]

12:27.460 --> 12:30.120
Well, I-I once read
in an incredible article

12:30.120 --> 12:31.880
that, um...

12:31.880 --> 12:34.380
"life is complicated,
but sometimes

12:34.380 --> 12:37.580
you're better off
embracing the mess

12:37.580 --> 12:40.040
than trying
to clean it all up."

12:40.040 --> 12:42.540
Randy's right.
This needs work.

12:42.540 --> 12:44.120
[ Laughs ]

12:44.120 --> 12:47.460
[ Ukulele playing ]

12:47.460 --> 12:50.540
Between this footage
of our friends with their kids,

12:50.540 --> 12:52.500
the stuff that we're
gonna get at Sophie's
softball game tomorrow,

12:52.500 --> 12:55.120
this video is going to be
unbelievable.

12:56.420 --> 12:59.080
You know
what's also unbelievable?

12:59.080 --> 13:01.080
That this could be us
one day soon.

13:01.080 --> 13:03.000
That we could have a kid

13:03.000 --> 13:05.290
who's gonna look to us
for all the answers,

13:05.290 --> 13:07.000
and we may not
have all of them,

13:07.000 --> 13:09.120
but we are going to
shape their world

13:09.120 --> 13:12.380
almost as much as
they're gonna shape ours.

13:12.380 --> 13:14.500
I can't believe...

13:14.500 --> 13:16.290
that I didn't get that
on camera.

13:16.290 --> 13:18.290
Can you say all those things
again, but this time,

13:18.290 --> 13:19.920
over by the window
with the good lighting?

13:19.920 --> 13:21.380
And please don't squint.
I don't squint.

13:21.380 --> 13:23.120
You do.
I --
Oh, hey, guys!

13:23.120 --> 13:24.790
This is Jess.

13:24.790 --> 13:26.710
As promised,
she's a girl.

13:26.710 --> 13:28.170
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, I'm Rome.

13:28.170 --> 13:29.420
I'm Regina.

13:29.420 --> 13:31.460
Both:
And we're the Howards.

13:31.460 --> 13:32.710
Nice to meet you.

13:32.710 --> 13:34.080
You, too.

13:34.080 --> 13:35.750
Oh, yeah,
and if you guys are editing,

13:35.750 --> 13:38.000
we can totally work downstairs
in the common room.

13:38.000 --> 13:39.420
That's very considerate.

13:39.420 --> 13:41.120
And, Jess, you're welcome
to stay for dinner.

13:41.120 --> 13:42.830
Yeah,
we're having fish.

13:42.830 --> 13:43.710
Just for the halibut.

13:43.710 --> 13:45.040
[ Both laugh ]

13:45.040 --> 13:46.790
That's my first dad joke.

13:48.420 --> 13:49.080
Have fun.

13:50.420 --> 13:51.420
Yeah.

13:51.420 --> 13:52.290
Sorry.

13:52.290 --> 13:53.540
Tough crowd.

13:53.540 --> 13:56.420
♪♪

13:56.420 --> 13:58.250
[ Sniffs ]

13:58.250 --> 13:59.670
Just keep 'em coming,
man.

13:59.670 --> 14:00.830
Yeah, sure thing.

14:00.830 --> 14:02.880
♪♪

14:02.880 --> 14:06.500
♪ We're lighting the room,
I can feel their eyes ♪

14:06.500 --> 14:08.000
[ Sighs ]

14:08.000 --> 14:09.670
♪ Let's embrace it ♪

14:09.670 --> 14:10.710
Oh, crap.

14:10.710 --> 14:11.710
No.

14:11.710 --> 14:12.960
No, no, no, no.

14:12.960 --> 14:14.580
Hey, if, uh, uh --

14:14.580 --> 14:17.000
if you like and then un-like
a picture really quickly,

14:17.000 --> 14:18.170
does the person know?

14:18.170 --> 14:19.790
Not unless they were online
when you did it.

14:20.960 --> 14:22.750
Are you stalking an ex?

14:22.750 --> 14:24.540
No!

14:24.540 --> 14:26.750
Just checking out
this guy she's dating.

14:26.750 --> 14:28.920
Something off
about this dude.

14:28.920 --> 14:30.250
He's nice.

14:30.250 --> 14:32.210
Too nice, you know?

14:32.210 --> 14:35.960
Like a...smiley face emoji
took human form.

14:35.960 --> 14:38.290
Did you check out
this guy's social media?

14:38.290 --> 14:41.290
Yeah. All his accounts
are private.

14:41.290 --> 14:44.500
Ran a search on the Web.
Nothing unusual came up.

14:44.500 --> 14:47.710
Okay, yeah, but did you check
the results on page 1 or page 9?

14:47.710 --> 14:49.170
What?

14:49.170 --> 14:50.000
Tagging in.

14:51.290 --> 14:53.330
[ Chuckles softly ]
All right.

14:53.330 --> 14:56.170
You seem unusually
invested in this.

14:56.170 --> 14:58.040
Well,
you should be, too.

14:59.880 --> 15:01.710
Check this out.

15:01.710 --> 15:03.250
[ Sighs ]

15:04.460 --> 15:05.960
What the hell?

15:05.960 --> 15:08.080
You are so welcome.

15:09.710 --> 15:12.250
Excited to make a child
part of our fam--

15:13.750 --> 15:16.170
Hey.
How'd the studying go?

15:16.170 --> 15:17.290
Good.

15:17.290 --> 15:19.330
[ Chuckles ]
Where are you going?

15:19.330 --> 15:20.750
Bed.

15:20.750 --> 15:22.580
But it's 6:30.

15:22.580 --> 15:24.920
And you sleep out here, girl.
[ Chuckles ]

15:24.920 --> 15:26.580
[ Coughs ]

15:26.580 --> 15:27.880
[ Retches ]

15:27.880 --> 15:29.460
[ Vomits ]

15:29.460 --> 15:31.540
I don't think
they were studying down there.

15:31.540 --> 15:32.290
Ya think?

15:35.750 --> 15:37.580
Regina:
You're gonna be okay, sweetie.

15:37.580 --> 15:39.580
[ Vomits, coughs ]
Oh, God.

15:39.580 --> 15:40.710
I'm not so sure about me.

15:40.710 --> 15:42.000
[ Groans ]

15:42.000 --> 15:43.620
Okay, baby, here.

15:43.620 --> 15:45.500
Hold this for a second, okay?
I'll be right back.

15:45.500 --> 15:46.620
[ Groaning ]

15:46.620 --> 15:47.790
Come on.

15:47.790 --> 15:49.710
Okay, here's the plan --

15:49.710 --> 15:51.210
one of us
has to keep an eye on her

15:51.210 --> 15:52.880
while the other one
calls Delilah

15:52.880 --> 15:54.790
and tells her what her daughter
did on our watch.

15:54.790 --> 15:56.250
[ Sophie coughs ]

15:56.250 --> 15:57.670
Good luck in there.

15:57.670 --> 15:59.920
[ Sighs ]
Okay. Thanks for that.

15:59.920 --> 16:02.040
Who loves being awake?

16:02.040 --> 16:03.580
We do! We d--

16:03.580 --> 16:05.880
No, no, no, no!
Don't fall asleep!

16:05.880 --> 16:07.080
Mm. No, no, no, no.

16:07.080 --> 16:10.000
No, not enough.
Not now.

16:10.000 --> 16:13.210
Alexa, play
baby Charlie's dance mix.

16:13.210 --> 16:14.540
[ Gasps ]
We're gonna party.

16:14.540 --> 16:16.000
Alexa: Playing
baby Charlie's dance mix.

16:16.000 --> 16:18.380
We're gonna party.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

16:18.380 --> 16:20.380
Here we go. Here we go.
Here we go.

16:20.380 --> 16:21.920
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪
♪ ...the dogs out? ♪

16:21.920 --> 16:23.960
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

16:23.960 --> 16:25.960
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

16:25.960 --> 16:27.670
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

16:27.670 --> 16:28.790
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪
♪ Who let the dogs -- ♪

16:28.790 --> 16:30.120
Hello.
Rome: Hey, D.

16:30.120 --> 16:31.670
Is that
"Who Let the Dogs Out?"

16:31.670 --> 16:33.040
Eh? What? No!

16:33.040 --> 16:35.250
Alexa, stop the music.

16:35.250 --> 16:36.960
Alexa: Okay.

16:36.960 --> 16:38.250
[ Clears throat ]
What's up, Rome?

16:38.250 --> 16:40.580
Not much.
Not much at all.

16:40.580 --> 16:42.790
Well, now that I have you,
might as well give you
a little update on Sophie.

16:42.790 --> 16:44.750
Did she miss her curfew
last night?

16:44.750 --> 16:46.290
Not exactly.

16:46.290 --> 16:47.670
Uh...

16:47.670 --> 16:49.960
Sophie's actually been here,
studying, the whole time.

16:49.960 --> 16:51.460
Well, at least
we thought she was studying.

16:51.460 --> 16:52.920
Her friend Jess came over.

16:52.920 --> 16:55.290
Ugh. That girl is
nothing but trouble.

16:55.290 --> 16:56.540
She is.

16:56.540 --> 16:58.710
She really is.

16:58.710 --> 17:00.420
On a related note...

17:03.120 --> 17:04.960
Trouble snuck some wine
into our place,

17:04.960 --> 17:07.460
and she and Sophie got drunk
in the common room.

17:07.460 --> 17:09.040
What?!

17:09.040 --> 17:11.460
Now, don't worry.
Sophie is safe.
[ Sighs ]

17:11.460 --> 17:14.920
Although she and our bathroom
are paying the price right now.

17:14.920 --> 17:16.500
Maybe I should come over.

17:16.500 --> 17:17.790
No, no. No.

17:17.790 --> 17:19.920
I just wanted to let you know
what happened.

17:19.920 --> 17:21.670
That's the update.
You've been updated.

17:21.670 --> 17:22.960
Now back to
your dance party.

17:22.960 --> 17:24.500
Let them dogs out, girl!

17:24.500 --> 17:25.580
Sophie's gonna be fine.

17:25.580 --> 17:27.880
[ Sophie vomits, coughs ]

17:27.880 --> 17:29.960
And, hopefully,
so will I.

17:31.500 --> 17:33.750
I just don't understand
why you pushed Auggie.

17:33.750 --> 17:35.250
He's a friend of yours.

17:37.500 --> 17:38.960
Hey.

17:38.960 --> 17:40.000
Hey, Theo.

17:40.000 --> 17:42.750
Let's put down the Legos.

17:42.750 --> 17:44.750
Talk to me.

17:44.750 --> 17:46.080
What's going on?

17:49.580 --> 17:51.420
Nothing.

17:51.420 --> 17:57.500
♪♪

17:57.500 --> 18:03.880
♪♪

18:03.880 --> 18:05.290
[ Whispering ] Hi.

18:05.290 --> 18:06.040
Hey.

18:06.040 --> 18:07.710
What are you doing here?

18:07.710 --> 18:10.330
I have exactly 47 minutes until
she goes down for the night,

18:10.330 --> 18:11.920
and I need to make sure
Sophie's okay.

18:11.920 --> 18:13.420
Not happening.

18:13.420 --> 18:15.000
What? What do you mean,
"Not happening"?

18:15.000 --> 18:16.710
I mean, your --
your body is not --

18:16.710 --> 18:18.120
[ Grunts ]

18:18.120 --> 18:19.620
...is not going through
that door.

18:19.620 --> 18:21.380
God. When did you get
so strong?

18:21.380 --> 18:23.380
Power Pilates twice a week.
At this point, I'm addicted.

18:23.380 --> 18:27.540
D, the whole point of this reset
is to re-set.

18:27.540 --> 18:30.580
She can't see you
be concerned about her.

18:30.580 --> 18:31.580
Right.

18:31.580 --> 18:32.710
Yeah.

18:32.710 --> 18:33.830
You're right.

18:33.830 --> 18:35.420
Hi.

18:35.420 --> 18:36.920
Would you stop?

18:36.920 --> 18:38.580
You're only gonna
make me hurt you.

18:38.580 --> 18:41.670
And besides,
if you go in there right now,

18:41.670 --> 18:43.250
what message
are you sending?

18:43.250 --> 18:44.750
[ Sighs ]

18:44.750 --> 18:46.250
[ Chuckles ]

18:46.250 --> 18:48.040
It's just like
sleep-training Charlie.

18:49.420 --> 18:50.830
This is Sophie's way

18:50.830 --> 18:54.420
of kicking and screaming
and testing me,

18:54.420 --> 18:57.500
and if I go through that door,
she wins.

18:57.500 --> 18:58.580
Exactly.

18:59.960 --> 19:02.540
But if I can't go in,
you need to do what I can't.

19:02.540 --> 19:03.920
Oh, believe me,
she's gonna find out

19:03.920 --> 19:05.920
that there are consequences
for her actions.

19:05.920 --> 19:07.540
Perfect.

19:07.540 --> 19:09.670
[ Chuckles ]

19:09.670 --> 19:11.500
But also, you need to
set limits for her

19:11.500 --> 19:13.710
so she knows
you can protect her.

19:13.710 --> 19:16.880
And more importantly,
that she's worth protecting.

19:18.710 --> 19:20.830
You're such a good mom.

19:20.830 --> 19:23.920
So good that my daughter
lives in your apartment.

19:23.920 --> 19:25.210
[ Chuckles ]

19:27.500 --> 19:28.880
[ Bell jingles ]

19:31.170 --> 19:32.330
That's okay, Max.
I got this.

19:32.330 --> 19:33.380
[ Door closes ]

19:33.380 --> 19:35.330
Gary. What's up?

19:35.330 --> 19:36.920
If you're here to pay me back
for those cookies,

19:36.920 --> 19:38.330
forget about it --
my treat.

19:38.330 --> 19:40.880
[ Chuckles ]

19:40.880 --> 19:42.620
I know what you're hiding.

19:42.620 --> 19:45.580
[ Scoffs ] What are you --
What are you talking about?

19:45.580 --> 19:48.120
There's a wrongful death suit
against you, man.

19:49.380 --> 19:52.920
From the family
of Chloe Myers.

19:52.920 --> 19:55.250
Now, would that be
the same Chloe

19:55.250 --> 19:56.880
that you were engaged to?

19:56.880 --> 19:58.330
Yeah, it is. Yeah.

19:58.330 --> 20:00.790
Does Maggie know
what you did?

20:00.790 --> 20:03.290
Is that not really what you two
talk about on your little dates?

20:04.960 --> 20:06.670
You're right.
You're right.

20:06.670 --> 20:08.620
Describing how you murdered
your fiancée

20:08.620 --> 20:10.000
is probably not
the best foreplay.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.580
Y-You don't know anything.

20:11.580 --> 20:13.120
Ooh-hoo!

20:13.120 --> 20:15.670
Based on how angry you're
getting, I think maybe I do.

20:15.670 --> 20:17.960
Maggie and I
are not together.

20:17.960 --> 20:19.790
But you know
what we do talk about?

20:19.790 --> 20:21.920
We talk about
what a mess you are,

20:21.920 --> 20:23.420
and no wonder
she wanted out.

20:23.420 --> 20:28.000
♪♪

20:28.000 --> 20:30.170
Hey!
What's going on?!

20:30.170 --> 20:32.830
♪♪

20:32.830 --> 20:34.080
I'm okay, Max.

20:34.080 --> 20:40.960
♪♪

20:40.960 --> 20:43.170
[ Sighs ]

20:43.170 --> 20:44.880
♪♪

20:44.880 --> 20:46.790
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

20:46.790 --> 20:53.120
♪♪

20:57.120 --> 20:58.830
[ Whispering ]
You ready?
[ Whispering ]
It's go time.

21:00.380 --> 21:02.000
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪
God!

21:02.000 --> 21:03.210
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪
Stop!

21:03.210 --> 21:04.540
Rise and shine!
[ Chuckling ] Come on.

21:04.540 --> 21:07.250
Come on, party girl. Time to
get ready for your big game.

21:07.250 --> 21:09.250
No. I'm not going.
Oh, yes, you are.

21:09.250 --> 21:12.460
Otherwise, you're gonna be
hearing this old-school jam
for the next four hours.

21:12.460 --> 21:13.670
♪ Who, who, who, who, who? ♪
Both:
♪ Who, who, who, who, who? ♪

21:13.670 --> 21:15.290
Okay, okay!
All right, okay!

21:15.290 --> 21:16.540
Just make it stop!

21:16.540 --> 21:18.000
[ Laughs ]
We leave in 20.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.420
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪

21:19.420 --> 21:20.880
We're gonna be
excellent parents.

21:20.880 --> 21:22.040
You know,
we got this in the bag.

21:22.040 --> 21:23.500
♪ Who let the dogs out? ♪

21:23.500 --> 21:24.790
[ Music stops ]
You know what?

21:24.790 --> 21:26.250
I should get my camera --

21:26.250 --> 21:28.330
Nope. Unh-unh.
Not going in the video.

21:30.580 --> 21:32.500
We'd have to reenact it
and -- yeah.
Keep it moving.

21:32.500 --> 21:33.670
Walk away.

21:33.670 --> 21:34.540
Walk away.

21:37.170 --> 21:39.960
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

21:39.960 --> 21:41.960
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hello?

21:41.960 --> 21:43.580
Trevor: Eddie, my man!
There you are.

21:43.580 --> 21:45.540
Ah, Trevor.

21:45.540 --> 21:47.420
Big sorry about yesterday.

21:47.420 --> 21:49.120
I was putting out fires
all day.

21:49.120 --> 21:50.540
But I finally got a chance

21:50.540 --> 21:52.080
to listen to those new tracks
you sent over.

21:52.080 --> 21:53.170
Oh, yeah?

21:53.170 --> 21:54.330
They're great, man.

21:54.330 --> 21:56.540
So great.

21:56.540 --> 21:58.460
But they're just...not...

21:58.460 --> 22:00.460
what we're looking for
right now.

22:00.460 --> 22:04.710
♪♪

22:04.710 --> 22:06.960
Thank you
for the phone call, Trevor,

22:06.960 --> 22:09.080
but you could've just
e-mailed that to me.

22:09.080 --> 22:12.500
I'm actually...calling about
that girl you met in the lobby.

22:12.500 --> 22:13.580
Dakota?

22:14.920 --> 22:17.290
Uh, what about her?

22:17.290 --> 22:18.960
Young woman:
Put me down on 2.

22:20.880 --> 22:22.460
[ Sighs ]

22:22.460 --> 22:23.460
[ Gulps ]

22:23.460 --> 22:24.880
[ Sighs ]

22:24.880 --> 22:28.830
[ Crowd cheering ]

22:28.830 --> 22:31.580
Hey, Soph, you want to look
about 10% less miserable?

22:31.580 --> 22:33.460
We're trying to show
that we're good with kids,

22:33.460 --> 22:35.210
not that
we crush their dreams.

22:36.540 --> 22:37.710
[ Sighs ]

22:37.710 --> 22:39.420
Nailed it!

22:40.830 --> 22:42.210
Hi.
Mm!

22:42.210 --> 22:44.250
How's Soph?
Mm...

22:44.250 --> 22:45.920
Maybe this could
be good for her.

22:45.920 --> 22:47.380
Maybe she'll never
drink again.

22:47.380 --> 22:48.750
Oh, no, she will.

22:48.750 --> 22:50.710
But hopefully, it bought us
another six months.

22:50.710 --> 22:51.880
Yeah.

22:51.880 --> 22:53.120
Oh.

22:53.120 --> 22:54.170
Um...
Hmm?

22:54.170 --> 22:55.210
For later.

22:55.210 --> 22:56.250
What's this?

22:56.250 --> 22:58.080
It's my way
of being there for her

22:58.080 --> 22:59.040
without actually
being there.

22:59.040 --> 23:00.250
It's her favorite.

23:00.250 --> 23:02.210
Ohh.

23:06.420 --> 23:08.620
First week on the job,
you let Sophie get drunk.

23:08.620 --> 23:10.040
Well done.

23:10.040 --> 23:12.580
What's next? You gonna
buy Danny some weed?

23:12.580 --> 23:15.170
[ Camera beeps ]
Okay, Gary,
we're gonna go again.

23:15.170 --> 23:16.830
But this time,
you mind saying something

23:16.830 --> 23:18.290
that would help me
get a child?

23:18.290 --> 23:20.750
Oh, that's right --
your adoption video.

23:20.750 --> 23:22.290
No wonder
you're all dressed up.

23:22.290 --> 23:25.250
Thought maybe Sophie's
softball game was business cazh.

23:25.250 --> 23:27.540
Gary, just look into the camera
and say --
Eat it.

23:27.540 --> 23:29.420
[ Chuckles ]

23:29.420 --> 23:31.670
Let's go, Soph!

23:31.670 --> 23:35.920
♪ Oh, oh,
let's be alone together ♪

23:35.920 --> 23:37.540
♪ Oh, oh... ♪
I just talked
to Maggie.

23:37.540 --> 23:40.420
I figured she'd have
some insight into what
Theo's going through.

23:40.420 --> 23:41.960
♪ You can go off on your own ♪
She offered
to come by later to --

23:41.960 --> 23:43.750
What are you
listening to?

23:43.750 --> 23:45.540
Oh, uh...

23:45.540 --> 23:47.380
apparently,
this is the future.

23:47.380 --> 23:48.920
I just talked to Trevor.
[ Song ends ]

23:48.920 --> 23:50.960
Oh, Trevor? That --
That's a good thing, right?

23:50.960 --> 23:52.960
[ Smacks lips ] No.

23:52.960 --> 23:54.380
He didn't call
to sign me.

23:54.380 --> 23:56.380
He called
'cause he wants me to supervise

23:56.380 --> 23:58.420
this millennial artist.

23:58.420 --> 23:59.830
Her name's Dakota.

23:59.830 --> 24:01.420
She's been
a bit of a problem for them,

24:01.420 --> 24:06.080
and he wants to hire me
to...help out.

24:06.080 --> 24:07.830
And after all that,
I told him I'd think about it,

24:07.830 --> 24:09.380
but there is no way.

24:10.670 --> 24:13.670
I cannot believe this is
what my career has come to.

24:13.670 --> 24:16.580
This Dakota...

24:16.580 --> 24:18.330
she sounds talented.

24:18.330 --> 24:19.620
What difference
does that make?

24:21.120 --> 24:23.580
You always say that making
great music is your dream.

24:23.580 --> 24:26.670
Maybe...this is a way
to do that.

24:26.670 --> 24:27.750
[ Scoffs ]

24:28.710 --> 24:30.170
[ Sighs ]

24:30.170 --> 24:33.920
I'm sorry. I get
that this is frustrating.

24:33.920 --> 24:36.670
But you should know

24:36.670 --> 24:40.120
that when I heard "Unexpected"
on the radio last year,

24:40.120 --> 24:42.920
I didn't care
that it wasn't your voice.

24:42.920 --> 24:44.670
They were your words.

24:44.670 --> 24:47.250
You made that.

24:47.250 --> 24:49.330
And I was so proud of you.

24:49.330 --> 24:50.380
[ Chuckles ]

24:50.380 --> 24:51.880
Right?

24:51.880 --> 24:53.790
[ Indistinct talking, applause ]

24:54.960 --> 24:56.790
[ Cheering ]

24:56.790 --> 25:00.830
Gary:
I know Rome is gonna hit "pause"
if Sophie starts to puke,

25:00.830 --> 25:02.540
but I want this
on video.

25:02.540 --> 25:03.580
[ Chuckles ]

25:03.580 --> 25:05.080
So...

25:05.080 --> 25:06.120
Regina: Huh.

25:07.080 --> 25:07.880
Mm-hmm.

25:07.880 --> 25:09.330
[ Cellphone beeps ]

25:09.330 --> 25:11.250
Any chance
you two didn't see that?

25:11.250 --> 25:12.540
Nope.

25:12.540 --> 25:14.330
[ Chuckles ]

25:14.330 --> 25:15.500
I --

25:15.500 --> 25:17.620
I just got
this ridiculous idea

25:17.620 --> 25:20.500
that something was going on
with her and Eric,

25:20.500 --> 25:21.670
and I went down a hole.

25:21.670 --> 25:22.830
It's fine.

25:22.830 --> 25:23.960
Mm.

25:27.750 --> 25:29.080
What was that?

25:29.080 --> 25:30.960
What -- What?
What was what?

25:30.960 --> 25:32.080
That face.
What was that?

25:33.920 --> 25:37.380
You would tell me
if something is going on, right?

25:37.380 --> 25:40.580
Gary, you two
really need to --

25:40.580 --> 25:42.040
You should just talk
to Maggie about it.

25:44.120 --> 25:47.040
Oh, I don't need to, because
you just answered my question.

25:47.040 --> 25:49.040
[ Sighs ]
No! I didn't --

25:49.040 --> 25:50.880
No.
I need to
go for a walk.

25:50.880 --> 25:52.580
Gary --
I'm just gonna get a pretzel,
all right?

25:52.580 --> 25:55.290
Can't a guy get a pretzel?

25:55.290 --> 25:56.960
[ Bat clanks ]

25:56.960 --> 25:59.040
[ Cheering ]

25:59.040 --> 26:00.330
Oh.
Here she goes.

26:00.330 --> 26:01.330
Drunk.

26:06.080 --> 26:07.170
[ Sighing ] Okay.

26:10.210 --> 26:11.500
Strike!

26:11.500 --> 26:14.290
Dixon! Get your head
in the game!

26:14.290 --> 26:15.500
Rome: Come on, Sophie.

26:16.960 --> 26:18.670
Who is that guy?

26:18.670 --> 26:20.580
I've never seen him before
in my life.

26:23.580 --> 26:25.920
Regina:
That was not pretty.
Umpire: Strike 2!

26:25.920 --> 26:28.000
Come on, Soph!
You got this!

26:28.000 --> 26:30.210
[ Cheering ]

26:30.210 --> 26:34.750
♪♪

26:34.750 --> 26:35.960
Young woman:
Come on, Soph!

26:37.460 --> 26:39.580
Young woman #2:
You got this, Soph!

26:39.580 --> 26:41.880
♪♪

26:41.880 --> 26:42.670
Yes!

26:42.670 --> 26:44.540
[ Cheering ]

26:44.540 --> 26:51.170
♪♪

26:51.170 --> 26:52.670
He's not a dad.
I needed that.

26:54.330 --> 26:55.620
Yes!

26:55.620 --> 26:58.120
Whoa! What the --
What the hell are you doing?

26:58.120 --> 26:59.460
I could ask you
the same thing.

26:59.460 --> 27:01.170
You think we wouldn't notice you
coming out here

27:01.170 --> 27:03.120
and taking pictures
of our girls?

27:03.120 --> 27:05.420
Look, man, it is not what
you think, all right? Just --

27:05.420 --> 27:07.880
What I think is that
you're hanging out in a place

27:07.880 --> 27:08.750
that you don't belong.

27:08.750 --> 27:09.830
Hey!

27:09.830 --> 27:11.080
Gary!

27:11.080 --> 27:12.540
Get up!
Are you --

27:12.540 --> 27:14.420
-Stop!
-Brad!

27:14.420 --> 27:17.000
Rome:
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Oh, my God.

27:17.000 --> 27:18.380
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

27:18.380 --> 27:19.750
Whoa, Gary. Stop.
Gary!

27:19.750 --> 27:21.120
I will kick your ass!

27:21.120 --> 27:22.500
Stop!
You're lucky, man!

27:22.500 --> 27:23.710
[ Laughs ]
Lucky day!

27:29.580 --> 27:32.040
This is ridiculous!
You should be arresting

27:32.040 --> 27:33.710
the racist dude who tried to
break my friend's camera!

27:33.710 --> 27:36.000
Guys,
just do what they say.

27:36.000 --> 27:39.250
Well, Gina, we got attacked
by some D-bag,

27:39.250 --> 27:42.250
and now the cops are putting us
in the back of a car!
[ Whispering ] Stop it.

27:42.250 --> 27:43.880
[ Groans ]

27:45.420 --> 27:48.040
[ Sighs ]
I can't believe this.

27:48.040 --> 27:50.080
Neither can I.

27:51.830 --> 27:54.580
What the hell
were you thinking?!

27:54.580 --> 27:56.120
What?

27:56.120 --> 27:57.960
[ Sighs ]

28:00.830 --> 28:04.080
Why do you keep
tightening those strings?

28:04.080 --> 28:06.120
Just makes me feel better.

28:08.580 --> 28:11.710
You know, your mom told me
what happened at school today.

28:13.670 --> 28:16.670
Was that other kid saying
mean things or something?

28:16.670 --> 28:19.250
No.
Auggie's my friend.

28:19.250 --> 28:21.670
What happened?

28:21.670 --> 28:24.210
Today was
desk-switching day.

28:24.210 --> 28:26.830
Why do we even have to
switch desks?

28:26.830 --> 28:28.210
That's my desk.

28:29.500 --> 28:31.080
Is that why
you pushed him?

28:34.580 --> 28:36.960
Everything keeps changing.

28:40.040 --> 28:42.750
You're right.
It does.

28:42.750 --> 28:46.210
You're dealing with
a lot of new things.

28:46.210 --> 28:48.880
New sister, new desk.

28:52.250 --> 28:53.880
Can I tell you
a little secret?

28:56.040 --> 28:58.250
I don't like change much,
either.

28:58.250 --> 29:00.250
But it's been good
for you.

29:01.790 --> 29:03.580
What do you mean?

29:03.580 --> 29:05.460
You were gonna die.

29:05.460 --> 29:07.500
But now you're not.

29:10.080 --> 29:12.120
I heard them
talking about it.

29:14.290 --> 29:15.920
They always think
I'm not listening,

29:15.920 --> 29:18.420
but I hear lots of things.

29:18.420 --> 29:19.540
Wow.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.580
That must...

29:21.580 --> 29:25.500
be really hard
to handle all by yourself.

29:25.500 --> 29:28.120
What do you do
when you hear stuff like that?

29:28.120 --> 29:31.290
Nothing, I guess.

29:31.290 --> 29:33.620
So you just
keep it all inside?

29:33.620 --> 29:38.790
♪♪

29:38.790 --> 29:40.830
Well...

29:40.830 --> 29:44.040
I find that when you hear
something upsetting,

29:44.040 --> 29:47.000
the best thing to do
is talk about it

29:47.000 --> 29:51.750
because if you leave
all of it unsaid,

29:51.750 --> 29:53.670
you'll burst.

29:53.670 --> 30:02.920
♪♪

30:02.920 --> 30:05.790
[ Police radio chatter ]

30:05.790 --> 30:08.460
Dude, all I did
was have your back.

30:08.460 --> 30:11.040
If that's having my back,
I don't need it.

30:12.920 --> 30:14.960
You want to know why I'm wearing
a button-down shirt

30:14.960 --> 30:16.620
to a kids' softball game?

30:16.620 --> 30:19.170
[ Sighs ] Because you're going
on camera and you're super vain?

30:19.170 --> 30:21.790
Because I knew I might be
the only black man here today.

30:21.790 --> 30:24.380
And I knew that
wearing a hoodie, like you,

30:24.380 --> 30:25.620
might put me and my wife
in danger.

30:25.620 --> 30:26.750
[ Scoffs ]

30:28.620 --> 30:31.540
I love you, bruh, but we live
in two different Bostons.

30:31.540 --> 30:33.290
Oh, come on, dude.
I'm half-Mexican.

30:33.290 --> 30:35.330
Passing for white!

30:36.920 --> 30:39.750
You ever notice
when I go in a grocery store,

30:39.750 --> 30:43.250
I telegraph everything
I take off the shelves?

30:43.250 --> 30:44.920
I never put my hands
in my pockets,

30:44.920 --> 30:46.920
and I practically staple
my receipt to my forehead

30:46.920 --> 30:48.290
when I walk out

30:48.290 --> 30:50.420
so everyone knows
I didn't steal anything.

30:50.420 --> 30:53.120
Half the time,
I don't even know I'm doing it.

30:54.830 --> 30:57.460
But that's my reality.

30:57.460 --> 30:59.120
That's how
my dad raised me.

31:00.670 --> 31:04.500
He taught me how to stay out
of situations like this.

31:06.420 --> 31:08.750
And that's how
I'll have to raise my child.

31:08.750 --> 31:10.920
And in one move,

31:10.920 --> 31:12.380
you've wrecked everything.

31:12.380 --> 31:13.790
I --

31:13.790 --> 31:15.000
[ Sighs ]

31:17.170 --> 31:19.290
It's one thing
to mess up your life...

31:21.170 --> 31:23.500
...but now you are
messing with mine.

31:23.500 --> 31:28.710
♪♪

31:28.710 --> 31:33.960
♪♪

31:33.960 --> 31:35.750
All right, Mr. Howard.
You're free to go.

31:35.750 --> 31:37.670
[ Police radio chatter ]

31:37.670 --> 31:45.120
♪♪

31:45.120 --> 31:50.710
♪♪

31:50.710 --> 31:52.120
What about me?!

31:52.120 --> 31:59.040
♪♪

31:59.040 --> 32:01.000
[ Scoffs ]

32:02.500 --> 32:04.830
So, all of this
over switching a desk?

32:04.830 --> 32:06.580
I mean, why wouldn't he
just talk to us?

32:06.580 --> 32:09.580
I don't think
it's totally about the desk.

32:09.580 --> 32:11.250
What do you mean?

32:11.250 --> 32:14.580
Uh, I'm --
I'm...not sure I should --

32:14.580 --> 32:15.460
Please.

32:17.790 --> 32:20.710
I think he's struggling.

32:20.710 --> 32:23.250
With you guys
almost getting divorced

32:23.250 --> 32:25.170
and then
getting back together

32:25.170 --> 32:28.790
and a new
baby half-sister --

32:28.790 --> 32:30.210
it's a lot
for him to process.

32:31.620 --> 32:33.330
Of course.

32:33.330 --> 32:36.620
But why won't he just
talk to us about it?

32:36.620 --> 32:40.920
Because the thing that he fears
the most is change,

32:40.920 --> 32:43.960
and I think
a part of him is worried

32:43.960 --> 32:47.880
that if he questions
the way things are,

32:47.880 --> 32:49.080
they'll change again.

32:51.120 --> 32:54.500
I'm going to refer you
to my colleague Susan.

32:54.500 --> 32:56.170
She will be able to help.

32:56.170 --> 32:57.290
Um...

32:57.290 --> 32:58.790
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

32:58.790 --> 33:01.380
I have her card here.

33:01.380 --> 33:02.830
Excuse me.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

33:02.830 --> 33:04.710
Hello?

33:04.710 --> 33:06.920
Yes, I'll accept.

33:06.920 --> 33:08.120
Who is it?

33:08.120 --> 33:09.170
It's Gary.

33:09.170 --> 33:11.080
Hey. U-Uh --

33:11.080 --> 33:12.460
You what?

33:12.460 --> 33:13.330
Okay.

33:13.330 --> 33:15.210
I'll be right there.

33:15.210 --> 33:16.330
[ Sighs ]
[ Cellphone beeps ]

33:16.330 --> 33:18.120
What is it now?

33:18.120 --> 33:20.620
Gary's been...arrested.

33:23.420 --> 33:26.120
Oh, Katherine, I'm sorry
for dragging you out here.

33:26.120 --> 33:27.620
You're the only lawyer
I know,

33:27.620 --> 33:29.790
and I saw 10 guys
and one open-air toilet,

33:29.790 --> 33:30.710
and, uh, I panicked.

33:30.710 --> 33:31.790
[ Chuckles ]

33:32.750 --> 33:35.000
Oh...great.

33:35.000 --> 33:36.960
I was hoping
you'd be here.

33:36.960 --> 33:38.750
Did you bring any
of my other exes to see this?

33:38.750 --> 33:40.120
Maggie: I'm not here
as your ex-girlfriend.

33:40.120 --> 33:41.830
I'm here as your friend.

33:41.830 --> 33:43.580
I'm...worried about you.

33:43.580 --> 33:45.290
Oh, well, thanks for that,

33:45.290 --> 33:47.290
but, uh,
we were never friends.

33:47.290 --> 33:49.250
I mean,
not like you and Eric.

33:49.250 --> 33:51.120
By the way...

33:51.120 --> 33:53.540
there's something off
about that guy.

33:53.540 --> 33:55.540
I don't trust him,
and you shouldn't, either.

33:55.540 --> 33:58.290
Gary, this is not okay.

33:58.290 --> 33:59.750
You need to
talk to somebody.

34:01.210 --> 34:02.960
Well...

34:02.960 --> 34:05.580
that somebody
is not gonna be you.

34:05.580 --> 34:08.670
But here's the good news --
you did it.

34:08.670 --> 34:11.830
I saved your life,
you picked me up from jail,

34:11.830 --> 34:13.960
so...

34:13.960 --> 34:15.210
we're even.

34:18.830 --> 34:21.790
[ Siren wails ]

34:21.790 --> 34:23.210
Hang on a second.

34:24.620 --> 34:25.880
How dare you.

34:25.880 --> 34:27.830
What?

34:27.830 --> 34:29.880
She's here because
she cares about you.

34:29.880 --> 34:31.500
I mean, we all do.

34:31.500 --> 34:35.000
Katherine, the last thing
I need right now

34:35.000 --> 34:36.830
is another lecture, okay?

34:36.830 --> 34:38.960
Well, that's too bad,
because you're getting one.

34:38.960 --> 34:40.420
[ Sighs ]

34:40.420 --> 34:42.960
When Eddie and I made you
Theo's guardian,

34:42.960 --> 34:45.790
it was not a decision
we took lightly.

34:45.790 --> 34:47.710
Out of everyone
in the world,

34:47.710 --> 34:51.250
we thought you were the one
best equipped to raise our son

34:51.250 --> 34:53.880
in case
something happened to us.

34:53.880 --> 34:55.960
Well, we were wrong.

34:55.960 --> 34:57.460
How could you possibly
take care of him

34:57.460 --> 34:59.170
when you can't even
take care of yourself?

35:00.960 --> 35:02.670
Find your own ride home.

35:06.250 --> 35:07.620
See ya.

35:07.620 --> 35:11.330
♪♪

35:15.790 --> 35:18.580
Hey, D, okay.
What do you think about this?

35:18.580 --> 35:21.170
Uh, "After a loss, sometimes
the hardest part of moving on

35:21.170 --> 35:22.920
isn't having to change yourself.

35:22.920 --> 35:26.880
It's accepting the fact
that you can't change others."

35:28.670 --> 35:31.960
N-No, it's, uh...

35:31.960 --> 35:34.670
It's about my family.

35:34.670 --> 35:37.380
But...

35:37.380 --> 35:39.620
Yeah, I guess
it could be about him, too.

35:46.330 --> 35:48.670
I'm sorry
I pushed Auggie yesterday.

35:50.670 --> 35:53.000
We know you are, bud.

35:53.000 --> 35:58.080
We know there is a lot
going on right now.

35:58.080 --> 36:00.000
But...

36:00.000 --> 36:03.290
you can talk to us
about anything.

36:03.290 --> 36:05.710
Like Dad's new job?

36:05.710 --> 36:07.000
Oh.

36:07.000 --> 36:09.210
You know about that?

36:09.210 --> 36:11.120
I heard you talking
earlier.

36:12.830 --> 36:15.330
Does this mean you're not
gonna be home as much?

36:15.330 --> 36:17.460
Oh, bud. Uh...

36:17.460 --> 36:19.460
Uh, well...

36:19.460 --> 36:22.880
Dad, you should
probably sit down

36:22.880 --> 36:26.330
and tell us everything
about this new job

36:26.330 --> 36:29.880
so that we can know
exactly what the plan is.

36:29.880 --> 36:32.790
That is a great idea.

36:32.790 --> 36:37.580
So, I am gonna be working with
this super cool new artist.

36:37.580 --> 36:39.250
Her name is Dakota.

36:39.250 --> 36:41.330
And you are
gonna love her.

36:44.880 --> 36:46.170
[ Clears throat ]

36:47.580 --> 36:49.380
It's hot.
Be careful.

36:49.380 --> 36:50.330
Thanks.

36:52.620 --> 36:54.170
Listen...

36:54.170 --> 36:57.170
I want to be
really clear.

36:57.170 --> 36:59.120
If you're gonna live
in this house,

36:59.120 --> 37:01.710
there are rules,
and you have to follow them.

37:02.960 --> 37:04.000
Yeah, I know.

37:04.000 --> 37:05.460
I'm...

37:05.460 --> 37:07.120
I'm really sorry.

37:07.120 --> 37:08.670
Just so you know,

37:08.670 --> 37:10.710
we're not being tough on you
because we don't care.

37:13.210 --> 37:15.080
We're being tough on you
because we do.

37:16.620 --> 37:17.580
Sophie...

37:18.830 --> 37:20.380
...you matter.

37:20.380 --> 37:27.620
♪♪

37:27.620 --> 37:29.040
This is my favorite,
by the way.

37:29.040 --> 37:30.250
[ Both chuckle ]

37:30.250 --> 37:31.670
How'd you know?

37:31.670 --> 37:33.500
I didn't.

37:33.500 --> 37:40.580
♪♪

37:40.580 --> 37:47.460
♪♪

37:47.460 --> 37:49.080
Rome:
They say that parenting is

37:49.080 --> 37:51.670
a series
of impossible challenges.

37:53.580 --> 37:56.880
♪ Cold light wakes me
in the morning ♪

37:56.880 --> 37:58.710
♪ Your side is empty ♪

37:58.710 --> 38:02.330
♪ I was calling out to you ♪

38:02.330 --> 38:05.500
♪ I was calling out to you ♪

38:05.500 --> 38:07.250
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

38:07.250 --> 38:10.920
♪ There's broken bottles
around me on the floor ♪

38:10.920 --> 38:14.210
♪ There's broken bottles around
me like a Technicolored you ♪

38:14.210 --> 38:16.290
How do you teach your kids
independence...

38:16.290 --> 38:19.250
♪ Technicolored you ♪

38:19.250 --> 38:20.540
Theo: She's really good.

38:20.540 --> 38:23.580
♪ Left your number on my bed ♪

38:23.580 --> 38:26.670
♪ Saying this is all
you gotta do ♪

38:26.670 --> 38:28.460
Rome: ...while letting them know
that they're not alone?

38:28.460 --> 38:30.580
♪ ...that my phone went dead ♪

38:30.580 --> 38:33.000
♪ Oh, I would do it again,
I'd do it again ♪

38:33.000 --> 38:34.620
♪ Mm, mm, mm ♪

38:34.620 --> 38:38.830
♪ And all of the nights
and all of the days ♪

38:38.830 --> 38:42.000
♪ Yeah, we're watching them
fading away ♪

38:42.000 --> 38:46.040
♪ And, oh, what a life
when you're rolling the dice ♪

38:46.040 --> 38:49.420
♪ When I'm gambling
all of the time ♪

38:49.420 --> 38:51.670
♪ But I don't need your love ♪

38:51.670 --> 38:53.120
[ Click ]

38:53.120 --> 38:56.170
♪ I just need you
talking next to me ♪

38:56.170 --> 38:58.250
♪ When I wake up, wake up ♪

38:58.250 --> 39:00.000
♪ Talking next to me
when I wake up... ♪

39:00.000 --> 39:03.960
How do you teach them
to let go of the past...

39:03.960 --> 39:07.500
♪ When I'm hungover, too ♪

39:07.500 --> 39:10.330
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
...while encouraging them
to embrace the unknown future?

39:10.330 --> 39:13.420
♪♪

39:13.420 --> 39:17.170
♪ 'Cause you're the only one
who comes when I'm lonely ♪

39:17.170 --> 39:22.580
♪ You're the only one who comes
when I'm lonely for you ♪

39:22.580 --> 39:24.920
♪ When I'm lonely for you ♪

39:24.920 --> 39:27.580
♪♪

39:27.580 --> 39:34.750
♪ All that I need
is a sweet escape ♪

39:34.750 --> 39:39.120
♪ And all of the nights
and all of the days ♪

39:39.120 --> 39:41.880
♪ Yeah, we're watching them
fading away ♪

39:41.880 --> 39:45.920
♪ And, oh, what a life
when you're rolling the dice ♪

39:45.920 --> 39:49.580
♪ When I'm gambling
all of the time ♪

39:49.580 --> 39:52.960
♪ But I don't need your love ♪

39:52.960 --> 39:54.830
♪ I just need your ♪

39:54.830 --> 39:57.120
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

39:57.120 --> 39:58.670
♪ I'm leaving now ♪

39:58.670 --> 40:01.580
♪♪

40:01.580 --> 40:03.920
♪ And oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

40:03.920 --> 40:05.250
♪ I'm leaving now ♪

40:05.250 --> 40:08.210
How do you teach them
to admit defeat...

40:08.210 --> 40:11.000
♪ And oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

40:11.000 --> 40:12.080
♪ I'm leaving now ♪

40:12.080 --> 40:15.000
[ Metal creaks ]

